.TH "radeon_gtt_location" 9 "radeon_gtt_location" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
radeon_gtt_location \- try to find GTT location
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" radeon_gtt_location
.BI "(struct radeon_device *rdev "  ","
.BI "struct radeon_mc *mc "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "rdev" 12
radeon device structure holding all necessary informations
.IP "mc" 12
memory controller structure holding memory informations
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Function will place try to place GTT before or after VRAM.

If GTT size is bigger than space left then we ajust GTT size.
Thus function will never fails.

